  "description": "Proof route for each apex promise badge. This file declares ONLY where each badge's proof lives (leaf spec, proof class, command, evidence files) and never the badge level. The badge level is declared once, in docs/specs/index.spec.md. build-surface-audit.mjs recomputes the observed level from these routes and fails the audit when the apex over-claims relative to what a route delivers. Match registry routes to apex badges by exact title. The audit is structural, not semantic: it does not prevent a proofSpec from pointing at an unrelated spec, and it does not verify the check blocks actually test this badge's behavior — leaf-spec review and `npm run lint:specs` running the checks themselves carry that correctness.",
